| Expression          | Coercion Steps              | Result              | Type    |
| ------------------- | --------------------------- | ------------------- | ------- |
| `5 + "5"`           | Number ‚Üí String             | `"55"`              | string  |
| `"5" - 2`           | String ‚Üí Number             | `3`                 | number  |
| `"5" * "2"`         | String ‚Üí Number             | `10`                | number  |
| `true + 1`          | Boolean ‚Üí Number (1)        | `2`                 | number  |
| `false + 1`         | Boolean ‚Üí Number (0)        | `1`                 | number  |
| `1 + null`          | null ‚Üí Number (0)           | `1`                 | number  |
| `1 + undefined`     | undefined ‚Üí NaN             | `NaN`               | number  |
| `null == undefined` | Special rule                | `true`              | boolean |
| `"0" == false`      | Both ‚Üí Number (0)           | `true`              | boolean |
| `0 == false`        | Boolean ‚Üí Number            | `true`              | boolean |
| `[] + []`           | Array ‚Üí String (`""`)       | `""`                | string  |
| `[] + {}`           | `"" + "[object Object]"`    | `"[object Object]"` | string  |
| `({} + [])`         | Object ‚Üí String             | `"[object Object]"` | string  |
| `{ } + []`          | Block + `+[]` ‚Üí Number      | `0`                 | number  |
| `[] == false`       | `[] ‚Üí "" ‚Üí 0`, `false ‚Üí 0`  | `true`              | boolean |
| `["5"] == 5`        | Array ‚Üí String ‚Üí Number     | `true`              | boolean |
| `[] == ![]`         | `![] ‚Üí false ‚Üí 0`, `[] ‚Üí 0` | `true`              | boolean |
| `NaN == NaN`        | No coercion match           | `false`             | boolean |
| `typeof NaN`        | JS quirk                    | `"number"`          | string  |
| `null == 0`         | Special rule                | `false`             | boolean |
| `null >= 0`         | null ‚Üí Number (0)           | `true`              | boolean |

üí° Key Rules to Remember:

+ operator ‚Üí If either operand is a string, concatenation happens; otherwise, numeric addition.
Other arithmetic operators (-, *, /, %) ‚Üí Convert operands to numbers.
Loose equality (==) ‚Üí Allows type coercion; strict equality (===) does not.
Falsy values: false, 0, "", null, undefined, NaN ‚Üí all become false in Boolean context.